As you know, I lost that game
great! We will fill the atmoshere of WC!
so, we will check it closer.
this 5 was popular in this WC
It was too obvious variant, and it must take lots of courage to gamble in that.
this point is not good for white
Especially, he must have known that I have studied it.
This has been a big question mark in past years.
Other 18th moves have proven to be losing except this one so far,
and this WC was supposed to put the end to this variant.
I had analysed it before WC,
This 19th move forces white to play as follows:
this 22nd move was a big question before WC.
Now, black has neutralized some of the white material below,
and created the dangerous space above
White does not have its own win either,
in order to create the counter-attack material
Probably the only way for white to save from black power.
maybe, we should also check about white's attack options
then white will be in trouble
I played these moves as black in Vosu renju camp,
I suppose you saw the game Sushkov-Yamaguchi
Tunnet must have leanred a lot from here :)
yamaguchi played the same losing 34th move
all is safe for black after this correct 39
and black wins as a result
and this tells you a lot about the nature of this variant
white is quite limited here in the corner as long as long as black has enough gun poweder up there to counter-attack
faint, how can you calculate so far...
Sinyov played the wise 34th move against me.
black seems to have no VCT after that,
and in case of any soft development move,
white's lower side might really become dangerous
and see how white may be strong because of absence of black's counter-attack
and white is really dangerously strong now
so, when I was thinking of move 35,
I was trying to find the way, to reduce white power by creating counter-attack.
he did not expect this move
Sinyov had had similar game as white before in Russia, against Nikonov I think,
and later Tunnet played same way against Sinyov
But I am not sure, was it mistake or not.
therefore white cannot be active yet
but it was hard to defend
after some time of thinking, Sinyov found the only defense - h10
It seems to me all other 36th move will lose.
why say it a only defense?
black had good left wing and right wing
the stone 35 makes this attack powerful
actually I knew black cannot win by that
I wanted to develop on the left side
but as long as white has k6 pointm
it is dangerous to lose tempo
if I could force white to play L7 earlier,
then I could afford losing the tempom
and play softly to the left side
Now, black is free to develop softly.
And now, I started to search for win.
if I can get the black stone to e7
leto, Alan, span, weigui, Volodymyr, slamduk, Padovan, shuwang, bawangwan, FIFAWORLDCUP, yyfcsd, alcore, luwenzhe, 8914643, whte, concord2497, moocheng, coco_yuang, pantrike.
then I can win in upper side
I knew the right win was safe enough
so I did not bother about counter-attack
i had a plan of making the d4,
and then the d4_d5 pair can reach d6, and then e7 is not far.
I played these 43, he put 44 actively.
and it was where I miscounted.. :(
and missed there is a VCT
first, I did not pay much attention to this problem,
because I was hoping to reach e7 by my own threats.
i cannot take my long waited e7
e7 is taken, but material of the top was already wasted
so whats the use of e7 without e11
so, I thought - maybe I dont need VCT style
I spent short time to confirm if there is white VCT on the right
and I convinced myself its safe enough to lose tempo
its such a nice move, I thought,
because after that white cannot defend anymore.
but I made a horrible miscalculation
its like the blind spot in brain
m7 was skipped from all my calculations!!
I was so sad,.. and angry at myself
how I did not focus enough
white cannot have VCT on the left
so I was careless, allowing white have that stone and then lose tempo after that
I was hoping for win in this game,
and keep the leadership of the championship,
but the way I played was bad
maybe simply here, since I dont need VCT
but I hurried to h4 too soon
although my win game became loss game,
it was interesting game by the planning
this game tells a lot about black potential and white potential
I thought I knew variant well enough to feel confident,
but I still lost the game
maybe not good to let white take e8 so early
These moves were made one round later,
but later, Sinyov too much wanted to win as white
i remember a palyer take a 4*4 by himself:)
So, this 5th is not sure win?
move 40 was not maybe not good
white has at least one block here already,
therefore the move 35 is not interesting
I did not complete the plan of this 35th move, but maybe the following games and tournaments can bring some answers into this variant
The difference between the times of before last WC and after last WC is,
maybe RT Ando PC crashed again...
before WC the variant was known until 19th move,
so there was 15 moves advancing in theory
I so much wanted to put a beautiful end to the variant,
where we dont need to force white to L7,
which means, we dont play to j9 now,
maybe he can use software to help him :)
it looks white is dangerous now on right
but perhaps other ideas can work
black has many great points up there,
but one must keep in eye on white's counter-attack.
so, if there will be found the move after which black can control that white's attack,
then we can perhaps complete this variant some day,
But until then, we need hard work.
Is this 11th the only good move?
Now, we will end the official part of the lesson, and then I can answer some questions.
